<h2 class="modal-header">6.0 MAKING PAYMENTS</h2>

<p>6.1	Payment.  Payment using the Services may only be made to merchants or third party services which have been on boarded and approved by Tupay.  When you make a payment from your linked card or mobile money wallet, Tupay will, upon conducting all necessary checks and verification, initiate the payment of the necessary amount including any applicable fees or charges, from your linked card or mobile money wallet which upon your authorization, i.e. customer entering the PIN in the payment’s In-App implementation, the payment will be effected.
</p>
<p>6.2	Payment Limits. We may, at our discretion, impose limits on the amount of payments you can send through the Tupay Services. The limits are displayed during entry in the event where as a customer you have input an amount either above maximum limit or below minimum limit.
</p>
<p>6.3	Linked Cards as a payment method. By adding a card payment type as a preferred payment method, linking a prepaid card and/or a debit card and/or a credit card as a payment mode in MasterPass or any other card processing payment mode availed, selecting it and inputting a card PIN or authorizing the payment in any other means availed by the card processing payment method for the purpose of making a payment for a service in Tupay; you are authorizing Tupay to initiate a charge on the card to obtain the relevant funds when the card is used as a Payment Mode pursuant to this Agreement. The respective card and the payment method Terms and conditions are applicable in respective card based payments in Tupay.
</p>
<p>6.4	Linked mobile money wallet or linked mobile banking as a payment method. By adding a mobile money or mobile banking payment type as a preferred payment method, selecting it as a payment mode in Tupay and inputting your PIN on the STK (SIM Tool Kit) Push or USSD Push for the purpose of making a payment for a service in Tupay; you are authorizing Tupay to initiate a charge on your linked mobile money wallet or linked mobile banking account to obtain the relevant funds when linked mobile money wallet or linked mobile banking is used as a payment mode pursuant to this Agreement. The respective linked mobile money or linked mobile banking Terms and conditions are applicable in respective mobile money or mobile banking based payments in Tupay.
</p>
<p>6.5	Merchant Processing Delay. When you send a payment to certain Merchants, you are providing an Authorization to Tupay to process your payment, complete the transaction and notify the merchant. The payment will be held as pending until the Merchant processes your payment. Some Merchants may delay processing your payment. In such an instance, your Authorization will remain valid for a few minutes after which we will initiate a reversal.
</p>
<p>6.6	Refused and Refunded Payments. When you send a payment, the merchant may reject it. Any unfulfilled or denied payment will be returned to your original Payment Method. We will return any unclaimed payment to you within the next working day of the date you initiated the payment. The reversal terms are as per the existing terms and conditions that apply for each Payment method in reference to reversal of principal bill amount and fees reversal. Tupay is a payment facilitator and has no control over the reversal process or terms of reversal for the respective payment method.
</p>
<p>6.7	Insufficient funds. You acknowledge and agree that if there are insufficient funds in your linked bank or mobile money wallet to make the necessary payment, Tupay will not authorize the payment and has the right to cancel the transaction. Tupay shall not be liable for any loss, damage or liability suffered or incurred by you from a transaction being cancelled due to insufficient funds in your linked bank card or mobile money.
</p>

